, sojourner, stranger.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"stranger(87x), alien(1x), sojourner(1x)"},"H1617":{"id":"H1617","lemma":"גֵּרָא","translit":"Gêrâʼ","pron":"gay-raw'","derivation":"perhaps from H1626 (גֵּרָה); a grain;","strongs_def":"Gera, the name of six Israelites","kjv_def":"Gera.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Gera(9x)"},"H1618":{"id":"H1618","lemma":"גָּרָב","translit":"gârâb","pron":"gaw-rawb'","derivation":"from an unused root meaning to scratch;","strongs_def":"scurf (from itching)","kjv_def":"scab, scurvy.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"scurvy(2x), scab(1x)"},"H1619":{"id":"H1619","lemma":"גָּרֵב","translit":"Gârêb","pron":"gaw-rabe'","derivation":"from the same as H1618 (גָּרָב); scabby;","strongs_def":"Gareb, the name of an Israelite, also of a hill near Jerusalem","kjv_def":"Gareb.","pos":"proper locative noun, proper masculine noun","usage":"Gareb(3x)"},"H1620":{"id":"H1620","lemma":"גַּרְגַּר","translit":"gargar","pron":"gar-gar'","derivation":"by reduplication from H1641 (גָּרַר);","strongs_def":"a berry (as if a pellet of rumination)","kjv_def":"berry.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"berry(1x)"},"H1621":{"id":"H1621","lemma":"גַּרְגְּרוֹת","translit":"gargᵉrôwth","pron":"gar-gher-owth'","derivation":"feminine plural from H1641 (גָּרַר);","strongs_def":"the throat (as used in rumination)","kjv_def":"neck.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"neck(4x)"},"H1622":{"id":"H1622","lemma":"גִּרְגָּשִׁי","translit":"Girgâshîy","pron":"ghir-gaw-shee'","derivation":"patrial from an unused name (of uncertain derivation);","strongs_def":"a Girgashite, one of the native tribes of Canaan","kjv_def":"Girgashite, Girgasite.","pos":"adjective","usage":"Girgashite(6x), Girgasite(1x)"},"H1623":{"id":"H1623","lemma":"גָּרַד","translit":"gârad","pron":"gaw-rad'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to abrade","kjv_def":"scrape.","pos":"verb","usage":"scrape(1x)"},"H1624":{"id":"H1624","lemma":"גָּרָה","translit":"gârâh","pron":"gaw-raw'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"properly, to grate, i.e. (figuratively) to anger","kjv_def":"contend, meddle, stir up, strive.","pos":"verb","usage":"meddle(4x), contend(3x), strive(1x)"},"H1625":{"id":"H1625","lemma":"גֵּרָה","translit":"gêrâh","pron":"gay-raw'","derivation":"from H1641 (גָּרַר);","strongs_def":"the cud (as scraping the throat)","kjv_def":"cud.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"cud(11x)"},"H1626":{"id":"H1626","lemma":"גֵּרָה","translit":"gêrâh","pron":"gay-raw'","derivation":"from H1641 (גָּרַר) (as in H1625 (גֵּרָה)); properly, (like H1620 (גַּרְגַּר)) a kernel (round as if scraped), i.e.","strongs_def":"a gerah or small weight (and coin)","kjv_def":"gerah.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"gerah(5x)"},"H1627":{"id":"H1627","lemma":"גָּרוֹן","translit":"gârôwn","pron":"gaw-rone'","derivation":"or (shortened) גָּרֹן; from H1641 (גָּרַר); (compare H1621 (גַּרְגְּרוֹת))","strongs_def":"the throat (as roughened by swallowing)","kjv_def":"[idiom] aloud, mouth, neck, throat.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"throat(4x), neck(2x), mouth(1x), aloud(1x)"},"H1628":{"id":"H1628","lemma":"גֵּרוּת","translit":"gêrûwth","pron":"gay-rooth'","derivation":"from H1481 (גּוּר);","strongs_def":"a (temporary) residence","kjv_def":"habitation.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"habitation(1x)"},"H1629":{"id":"H1629","lemma":"גָּרַז","translit":"gâraz","pron":"gaw-raz'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to cut off","kjv_def":"cut off.","pos":"verb"},"H1630":{"id":"H1630","lemma":"גְּרִזִים","translit":"Gᵉrizîym","pron":"gher-ee-zeem'","derivation":"plural of an unused noun from H1629 (גָּרַז) (compare H1511 (גִּזְרִי)), cut up (i.e. rocky);","strongs_def":"Gerizim, a mountain of Palestine","kjv_def":"Gerizim.","pos":"proper locative noun","usage":"Gerizim(4x)"},"H1631":{"id":"H1631","lemma":"גַּרְזֶן","translit":"garzen","pron":"gar-zen'","derivation":"from H1629 (גָּרַז);","strongs_def":"an axe","kjv_def":"ax.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"axe(4x)"},"