r","kjv_def":"rain, shower.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"rain(31x), shower(4x)"},"H1654":{"id":"H1654","lemma":"גֶּשֶׁם","translit":"Geshem","pron":"gheh'-shem","derivation":"or (prolonged) גַּשְׁמוּ; the same as H1653 (גֶּשֶׁם);","strongs_def":"Geshem or Gashmu, an Arabian","kjv_def":"Geshem, Gashmu.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Geshem(3x), Gashmu(1x)"},"H1655":{"id":"H1655","lemma":"גֶּשֶׁם","translit":"geshem","pron":"gheh'-shem","derivation":"(Aramaic) apparently the same as H1653 (גֶּשֶׁם);","strongs_def":"used in a peculiar sense, the body (probably for the (figuratively) idea of a hard rain)","kjv_def":"body.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"body(5x)"},"H1656":{"id":"H1656","lemma":"גֹּשֶׁם","translit":"gôshem","pron":"go'-shem","derivation":"from H1652 (גָּשַׁם); equivalent to H1653 (גֶּשֶׁם)","strongs_def":"{a shower}","kjv_def":"rained upon.","pos":"masculine noun, verb","usage":"rained(1x)"},"H1657":{"id":"H1657","lemma":"גֹּשֶׁן","translit":"Gôshen","pron":"go'-shen","derivation":"probably of Egyptian origin;","strongs_def":"Goshen, the residence of the Israelites in Egypt; also a place in Palestine","kjv_def":"Goshen.","pos":"proper locative noun","usage":"Goshen(15x)"},"H1658":{"id":"H1658","lemma":"גִּשְׁפָּא","translit":"Gishpâʼ","pron":"ghish-paw'","derivation":"of uncertain derivation;","strongs_def":"Gishpa, an Israelite","kjv_def":"Gispa.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Gispa(1x)"},"H1659":{"id":"H1659","lemma":"גָּשַׁשׁ","translit":"gâshash","pron":"gaw-shash'","derivation":"a primitive root; apparently","strongs_def":"to feel about","kjv_def":"grope.","pos":"verb","usage":"grope(2x)"},"H1660":{"id":"H1660","lemma":"גַּת","translit":"gath","pron":"gath","derivation":"probably from H5059 (נָגַן) (in the sense of treading out grapes);","strongs_def":"a wine-press (or vat for holding the grapes in pressing them)","kjv_def":"(wine-) press (fat).","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"winepress(3x), press(1x), winefat(1x)"},"H1661":{"